==Arabic alphabet==

===Letter===
'''{{ARchar|أ / ‍أ}}''' (’álifu hámzatin)

# The first letter of the [[Arabic]] alphabet is the small [[hamza]] ({{ARchar|[[ء]]}}) that sits on top of {{ARchar|[[أ]]}}, and the tall column is its bearer. The composite letter is called {{ARchar|[[الف]]}} (’álif) and  the hamza represents a [[glottal stop]] (ʔ). (For the pronunciation without hamza, see {{ARchar|[[ا]]}}.) It is followed by {{ARchar|[[ب]]}}.
# The first letter in traditional [[Abjad]] order, which is used in place of numerals for list numbering ([[Abjad numerals]]). It is followed by {{ARchar|[[ب]]}}.

[[Category:Abjad numerals|01]]

====Pronunciation====
'''Combined with [[fathah]]:'''
<font size="5">أ</font> — '''ʔa'''.


'''Combined with [[kasra]]:'''
<font size="5">إ</font> — '''ʔi'''.


'''Combined with [[damma]]:'''
<font size="5">{{ARchar|ﹸ}}</font><font size="5">أ</font> — '''ʔu'''.

